<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871224-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Statesman Group Inc.</HL><DD> 12/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> STTG SMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Statesman Group Inc. said that a subsidiary of Dallas-based Southmark Corp. has acquired a 4.9% stake in the company and may seek as much as 100% of its 5.5 million common shares outstanding.    The Des Moines, Iowa-based holding company with interests in insurance and financial services said Southmark's Pacific Standard Life Insurance Co. subsidiary disclosed its intentions in a recent filing with the Alabama Insurance Department. One of Statesman Group's largest insurance subsidiaries, Vulcan Life Insurance Co., is based in Birmingham, Ala.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Statesman Group shares rose $1.0625 to close at $4.9375. </TEXT></DOC>